        "description": "Typical for 1064 nm cleaning to ensure pulse overlap without excessive heat accumulation on Pyrex (melting point ~820°C); 50 kHz balances speed and thermal management; higher rates increase efficiency but risk stress. Source: Academic literature (J. Appl. Phys., 2020) on pulsed laser cleaning of borosilicates."
